io.hekate.cluster.seed

Class StaticSeedNodeProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.hekate.cluster.seed.StaticSeedNodeProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SeedNodeProvider

    public class StaticSeedNodeProvider
extends Object
implements SeedNodeProvider
    Seed node provider with a pre-configured static list of seed node addresses.

    This provider uses a fixed set of addresses that can be specified at construction time via StaticSeedNodeProviderConfig configuration object and can't be changed at runtime. Addresses can be specified via StaticSeedNodeProviderConfig.setAddresses(List) method that accepts a list of strings in a form of <host>:<port> (f.e. 192.168.39.41:10012).

    Below is the configuration example: 

    
StaticSeedNodeProviderConfig cfg = new StaticSeedNodeProviderConfig()
    .withAddress("192.168.39.41:10021") // Using IPv4 address
    .withAddress("my-host.my-company.com:10021") // Using host name
    .withAddress("[fe80::b573:dd7b:589:e010%17]:10021"); // Using IPv6 address

StaticSeedNodeProvider provider = new StaticSeedNodeProvider(cfg);

    See Also:
    ClusterServiceFactory.setSeedNodeProvider(SeedNodeProvider), SeedNodeProvider
